item.title: Project Euler - Problem 1 - Multiples of 3 and 5
item.description: As part of my effort to refresh my memory in the areas of algorithms, data structures and mathematics, I’m going to use problems from Project Euler. Now, let’s get to problem 1. /* Project Euler - Problem 1 - Multiples of 3 and 5 [ https://projecteuler.net/problem=1 ] If we list all the natural numbers below 10 that are multiples of 3 or 5, we get 3, 5, 6 and 9. The sum of these multiples is 23.
